<DOC><DOCNO> AP890225-0059 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-02-25-89 1117EST</FILEID><FIRST>r i AM-Mozambique     02-25 0130</FIRST><SECOND>AM-Mozambique,0132</SECOND><HEAD>Government Says 145 Rebels Killed in Southern Province This Year</HEAD><DATELINE>MAPUTO, Mozambique (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Government troops have killed 145 rebelfighters this year in the southern province of Inhambane, thenational news agency AIM reported Saturday.   AIM said government forces have overrun seven bases in theprovince that were held by the rebels of the Mozambique NationalResistance, AIM said, citing unidentified military sources.   The guerrillas have been fighting the Marxist government since1977. They have seriously damaged the economy with attacks on bothcivilian and military targets.   Mozambique is one of the poorest countries in the world, and thewar is the main cause of a nationwide food shortage that has leftabout 6 million of the country's 15 million people in need of foodaid.</TEXT></DOC>